[{"id":"algebra-st-e1","diff":"easy","type":"mc","q":"<p>Simplify by combining like terms: 5y + 9 &minus; 3y &minus; 4 + y</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["3y + 5","2y + 5","3y + 13","9y + 5","3y &minus; 5"],"answer":0,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>Combine y-terms: 5y &minus; 3y + y = 3y. Combine constants: 9 &minus; 4 = 5. Result: <strong>3y + 5</strong>.</p>"},
{"id":"algebra-st-e2","diff":"easy","type":"mc","q":"<p>Apply the distributive property: &minus;3(2x &minus; 5)</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["&minus;6x + 15","&minus;6x &minus; 15","6x &minus; 15","&minus;6x &minus; 5","&minus;5x + 15"],"answer":0,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>Multiply each term by &minus;3: &minus;3&middot;2x = &minus;6x and &minus;3&middot;(&minus;5) = +15. Result: <strong>&minus;6x + 15</strong>.</p>"},
{"id":"algebra-st-e3","diff":"easy","type":"mc","q":"<p>Evaluate 2x<sup>2</sup> + 3x &minus; 5 when x = &minus;3.</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["4","&minus;14","22","&minus;4","32"],"answer":0,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>2(&minus;3)<sup>2</sup> + 3(&minus;3) &minus; 5 = 2(9) &minus; 9 &minus; 5 = 18 &minus; 9 &minus; 5 = <strong>4</strong>.</p>"},
{"id":"algebra-st-e4","diff":"easy","type":"mc","q":"<p>Factor out the greatest common factor: 12x<sup>4</sup> &minus; 8x<sup>3</sup></p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["4x<sup>3</sup>(3x &minus; 2)","4x<sup>3</sup>(3x &minus; 8)","2x<sup>3</sup>(6x &minus; 4)","4x<sup>4</sup>(3 &minus; 2x)","6x<sup>3</sup>(2x &minus; 1)"],"answer":0,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>GCF of 12 and 8 is 4; lowest power of x is x<sup>3</sup>. So GCF = 4x<sup>3</sup>. Dividing: 12x<sup>4</sup>/4x<sup>3</sup> = 3x and 8x<sup>3</sup>/4x<sup>3</sup> = 2. Result: <strong>4x<sup>3</sup>(3x &minus; 2)</strong>.</p>"},
{"id":"algebra-st-m1","diff":"medium","type":"mc","q":"<p>Use FOIL to expand: (x &minus; 5)(x + 9)</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["x<sup>2</sup> + 4x &minus; 45","x<sup>2</sup> &minus; 4x &minus; 45","x<sup>2</sup> + 14x &minus; 45","x<sup>2</sup> + 4x + 45","x<sup>2</sup> &minus; 45"],"answer":0,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>F: x&middot;x = x<sup>2</sup>. O+I: 9x &minus; 5x = 4x. L: (&minus;5)(9) = &minus;45. Result: <strong>x<sup>2</sup> + 4x &minus; 45</strong>.</p>"},
{"id":"algebra-st-m2","diff":"medium","type":"qc","q":"<p>Compare the two quantities for any real number x.</p>","info":"","qa":"(x + 1)<sup>2</sup>","qb":"x<sup>2</sup> + 2x + 2","choices":[],"answer":1,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>Quantity A expands to x<sup>2</sup> + 2x + 1. Quantity B is x<sup>2</sup> + 2x + 2. Subtracting A from B leaves 1 for every value of x, so B is always exactly 1 greater. <strong>Quantity B is greater.</strong></p>"},
{"id":"algebra-st-m3","diff":"medium","type":"mc","q":"<p>Factor completely: 3x<sup>2</sup> &minus; 11x + 6</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["(3x &minus; 2)(x &minus; 3)","(3x &minus; 3)(x &minus; 2)","(3x + 2)(x + 3)","(3x &minus; 6)(x &minus; 1)","(3x &minus; 1)(x &minus; 6)"],"answer":0,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>Need factors of 3&middot;6 = 18 that sum to &minus;11: that's &minus;9 and &minus;2. Split: 3x<sup>2</sup> &minus; 9x &minus; 2x + 6 = 3x(x &minus; 3) &minus; 2(x &minus; 3) = <strong>(3x &minus; 2)(x &minus; 3)</strong>.</p>"},
{"id":"algebra-st-m4","diff":"medium","type":"mc","q":"<p>Simplify the rational expression: (x<sup>2</sup> &minus; 9) / (x<sup>2</sup> &minus; x &minus; 6)</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["(x + 3)/(x + 2)","(x &minus; 3)/(x + 2)","(x + 3)/(x &minus; 2)","(x &minus; 3)/(x &minus; 2)","(x + 3)/(x &minus; 3)"],"answer":0,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>Factor: numerator = (x &minus; 3)(x + 3); denominator = (x &minus; 3)(x + 2). Cancel the common (x &minus; 3): <strong>(x + 3)/(x + 2)</strong>.</p>"},
{"id":"algebra-st-m5","diff":"medium","type":"ne","q":"<p>If (a + b)<sup>2</sup> = 64 and a<sup>2</sup> + b<sup>2</sup> = 40, what is the value of ab?</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":[],"answer":12,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>(a + b)<sup>2</sup> = a<sup>2</sup> + 2ab + b<sup>2</sup> = 64. Substitute a<sup>2</sup> + b<sup>2</sup> = 40: 40 + 2ab = 64, so 2ab = 24 and ab = <strong>12</strong>.</p>"},
{"id":"algebra-st-h1","diff":"hard","type":"ne","q":"<p>If x<sup>2</sup> &minus; y<sup>2</sup> = 60 and x &minus; y = 5, what is the value of x + y?</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":[],"answer":12,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>x<sup>2</sup> &minus; y<sup>2</sup> = (x &minus; y)(x + y). So 60 = 5(x + y), giving x + y = 60/5 = <strong>12</strong>.</p>"},
{"id":"algebra-st-h2","diff":"hard","type":"mc","q":"<p>For which value of x does (x<sup>2</sup> &minus; 7x + 12) / (x<sup>2</sup> &minus; 9) = 0?</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["4","3","&minus;3","both 3 and 4","&minus;4"],"answer":0,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>A fraction equals 0 only when the numerator is 0 and the denominator is not. Numerator (x &minus; 3)(x &minus; 4) = 0 gives x = 3 or x = 4. But denominator (x &minus; 3)(x + 3) = 0 at x = 3 (undefined), so x = 3 is excluded. Only valid solution: <strong>x = 4</strong>.</p>"},
{"id":"algebra-st-h3","diff":"hard","type":"qc","q":"<p>Compare the two quantities for any real number x.</p>","info":"","qa":"(x &minus; 4)<sup>2</sup>","qb":"x<sup>2</sup> &minus; 16","choices":[],"answer":3,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>Quantity A = x<sup>2</sup> &minus; 8x + 16; Quantity B = x<sup>2</sup> &minus; 16. The difference A &minus; B = &minus;8x + 32 = &minus;8(x &minus; 4), which changes sign with x. At x = 0: A = 16, B = &minus;16 (A greater). At x = 10: A = 36, B = 84 (B greater). <strong>The relationship cannot be determined.</strong></p>"}]
